-- W.R. Berkley Says Storm Sandy to Cost as Much as $50 Million
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2012-12-13T22:50:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-13/w-r-berkley-says-storm-sandy-to-cost-as-much-as-50-million.html
W.R. Berkley Corp., the seller of
property-casualty insurance, said that losses from superstorm
Sandy will be as much as $50 million before tax.  Costs from the October storm that struck the U.S. Northeast
will be at least $40 million, the Greenwich, Connecticut-based
insurer said today in a statement distributed by  Business Wire .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  